### Render Create Schedule Atom (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/atoms/create-schedule.mdx

Demonstrates how to render the CreateSchedule atom, which provides a dialog interface for creating new availability schedules. It accepts props for customization, including specific class names for styling and callback functions for success and error handling.

```javascript
import { CreateSchedule } from "@calcom/atoms";

export default function CreateSchedule() {
  return (
    <>
      <CreateSchedule
        name="Create new schedule"
        customClassNames={{
          createScheduleButton: "bg-red-500 border-none my-4 mx-2 rounded-md",
        }}
      />
    </>
  )
}
```

