### Enable Date Overrides in Availability Settings Atom (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/atoms/availability-settings.mdx

Renders the AvailabilitySettings atom with date override capabilities enabled via the 'enableOverrides' prop. It provides callbacks for update/delete success and form state changes, allowing access to 'dateOverrides' within the form state. This feature lets users set specific availability for particular dates.

```javascript
import { AvailabilitySettings } from "@calcom/atoms";

export default function Availability() {
  return (
    <>
       <AvailabilitySettings
          enableOverrides={true}
          onUpdateSuccess={() => {
            console.log("Updated schedule successfully");
          }}
          onDeleteSuccess={() => {
            console.log("Deleted schedule successfully");
          }}
          onFormStateChange={(formState) => {
            console.log("Form state changed:", formState);
            // Access form data including dateOverrides: formState.dateOverrides
          }}
       />
    </>
  )
}
```

